  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Requesting message in group chat doesn't contain recipient name. There is no way to see to whom this message is sent, so any user can see it as it was sent to him. We need some indication in the message to show the recipient. In the image below, recipient and another member of the group chat see identical message and both can use it to send ether:\r\n![img_1914](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/27752740-40ec1c2a-5deb-11e7-8472-b5e8c707f483.JPG)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nRequesting message in the group chat specifies recipient username\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nRequesting message in the group chat looks similar to all members and all of them can use it to send ether.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nyou need to have group chat with 3 mebers\r\n- Open Status\r\n- as member1: request from member2 some ether in group chat\r\n- as member2: check how requesting message looks like and use it to send ether to member1 (it's expected that only member2 can use it or that message shows who is intended recipient - member2)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.8-56-gd743691+\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS",
